    {
      "id": "874fd12ec5b15a5440dee056f51ca791545d66a5",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 808,
        "name": "Shaun Tancheff",
        "email": "shaun.tancheff@hpe.com",
        "username": "stancheff"
      },
      "date": "2024-08-11 07:40:49.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "98730b1d8bad872f060d31e522a6ab69967fcab3",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 353,
        "name": "Li Dongyang",
        "email": "dongyangli@ddn.com",
        "username": "lidongyang"
      },
      "date": "2024-08-12 01:13:56.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nDidn't realise ubuntu could backport changes from upstream 6.4,\nbut are we looking at the same kernel source code?\nAfter checking every release including the SuSE ones I think only\nldiskfs-5.15.0-106-ubuntu20.series\nhas the upstream change and can apply the new patch.\n\nCan you confirm the distro release/kernel version you were using when the build error happens?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "cdd89c0bf791f5a64987408c2558f1eb8ac05a74",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2024-08-12 13:37:12.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nuname -r\n5.15.0-118-generic\n\nis what I'm running with and I see this breakage.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "f8f70d2b03013a79f19478b08f2b01bb40d40497",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2024-08-12 13:38:35.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nYes I didn't apply it to the earlier version of Ubuntu.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "1df85e73f90d202183527d499ca131ca2e80896e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 353,
        "name": "Li Dongyang",
        "email": "dongyangli@ddn.com",
        "username": "lidongyang"
      },
      "date": "2024-08-13 01:11:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: -Code-Review\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> uname -r\n> 5.15.0-118-generic\n> \n> is what I'm running with and I see this breakage.\n\nWhich matches what I found out that only ldiskfs-5.15.0-106-ubuntu20.series needs this, the rest doesn't have the upstream change ported and can not apply the ldiskfs patch.\n\nI will refresh 55896. Adding ext4-filename-encode.patch to 5.8 ubuntu series can still stay here.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "889546e3ec29471adfadf7ad528d3f4bb1ed106b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2024-08-14 14:39:15.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nAre you sure SUSE doesn't have the same issue? I can't say since I don't have SUSE servers but Shaun does which is why I added him. Shaun\ndoes LU-18080 break SuSE15?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "edd645ce0b70d451513146e9044808e803ec0742",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 353,
        "name": "Li Dongyang",
        "email": "dongyangli@ddn.com",
        "username": "lidongyang"
      },
      "date": "2024-08-15 02:20:11.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> Are you sure SUSE doesn't have the same issue? I can't say since I don't have SUSE servers but Shaun does which is why I added him. Shaun\n> does LU-18080 break SuSE15?\n\nI'm positive, just checked the SLES kernel source again.\nSLES15 SP4 and SP5 doesn't have the upstream change but looks like the upcoming SP6 does have it and need the new ldiskfs patch.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "d6b634ae4e0c73d3282883c6efc48679687ceded",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 808,
        "name": "Shaun Tancheff",
        "email": "shaun.tancheff@hpe.com",
        "username": "stancheff"
      },
      "date": "2024-08-15 07:38:26.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> Are you sure SUSE doesn't have the same issue? I can't say since I don't have SUSE servers but Shaun does which is why I added him. Shaun\n> does LU-18080 break SuSE15?\n\nUnfortunately sp4 and sp5 series need a refresh for other reasons. Fixing that it looks like sp5 (5.14.21-150500.55.65) and sp4 (5.14.21-150400.24.100) need the NO_CHECKS patch to build.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "caa96193b9c28c4f19ce09999536e8baf237e890",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 808,
        "name": "Shaun Tancheff",
        "email": "shaun.tancheff@hpe.com",
        "username": "stancheff"
      },
      "date": "2024-08-15 07:40:39.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> > Patch Set 1:\n> > \n> > Are you sure SUSE doesn't have the same issue? I can't say since I don't have SUSE servers but Shaun does which is why I added him. Shaun\n> > does LU-18080 break SuSE15?\n> \n> Unfortunately sp4 and sp5 series need a refresh for other reasons. Fixing that it looks like sp5 (5.14.21-150500.55.65) and sp4 (5.14.21-150400.24.100) need the NO_CHECKS patch to build.\n\nimo it would be better to just push a follow on refresh for SUSE 15 since it isn't building currently anyway.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
